00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:21,200
- What?
- Nah, it's just that we drank a lot of alcohol.

253
00:20:21,700 --> 00:20:24,500
Leaving this late, you'll probably
be really tired for class tomorrow.

254
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:29,000
- Oh...
- That's all there is to it...

255
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:32,900
I just want... to sleep with you.

256
00:20:38,300 --> 00:20:40,700
No, I mean it literally.

257
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:44,300
(Coach is calling)

258
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,000
Hello, Coach.

259
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:49,120
Kwon Jungwoo, where are you right now?

260
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:52,300
You have five minutes. Get
back here right away, understood?

261
00:21:03,700 --> 00:21:05,200
Looks like I have to head out first.

262
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:10,300
Did you get called back to the dorm?

263
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:12,000
There's a reason for that.

264
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:17,700
There are other reasons, too.

265
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:27,900
Got it, take care on your way.

266
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,000
I'm heading out.

267
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:22,100
Han Jiwon.

268
00:22:41,300 --> 00:22:43,500
Are you pushing yourself too hard?

269
00:22:44,900 --> 00:22:46,000
It's nothing...

270
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:54,000
Han Jiwon, Han Jiwon.

271
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:03,800
Senior.

272
00:23:06,700 --> 00:23:08,340
Because I heard you suddenly disappeared.

273
00:23:11,500 --> 00:23:13,500
Uh, hello?

274
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:17,000
You're Kwon Jungwoo, right?

275
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:19,719
The match was really exciting to watch.

276
00:23:19,720 --> 00:23:21,400
I'm a fan of yours.

277
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:29,199
Jiwon! The manager might be coming by later,
too. Can you stick around a bit longer?

278
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:30,649
Do you have something urgent going on?

279
00:23:30,650 --> 00:23:31,650
Hmm...

280
00:23:32,700 --> 00:23:34,300
Ah, no, that's not it...

281
00:23:35,700 --> 00:23:38,000
My ankle hurts a bit
from that roll just now.

282
00:23:39,300 --> 00:23:40,300
I want to take a break.

283
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:46,409
Hey, you don't have any more matches coming
up anyway. Why not just rest in the lounge?

284
00:23:46,410 --> 00:23:51,400
If the manager comes by later and you're not
here, that might not look so good, right?

285
00:23:52,500 --> 00:23:54,100
You get what I mean, right?

286
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:56,800
Ah.

287
00:23:58,100 --> 00:23:59,100
Got it.

288
00:24:00,700 --> 00:24:03,399
Yeah! Now that I think about it carefully.

289
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:06,560
Every year we have to show off our skills.
How come you can't handle it already?

290
00:24:07,300 --> 00:24:09,230
That would be really embarrassing for me.

291
00:24:09,930 --> 00:24:10,930
What?

292
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:13,200
Isn't this just a one-time thing?

293
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:17,200
No, that's not it, Jiwon.

294
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:20,600
That was just something
I said off the cuff.

295
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:26,239
There are so many kids who joined just to
see you. If you only perform this year...

296
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:27,240
Is this really okay?

297
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:31,600
Don't you think you're being a bit selfish?

298
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:35,520
- But last time we were talking about a cover shoot.
- A cover shoot?

299
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:37,900
I've already said thank you for that.

300
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:40,100
And also.

301
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:43,800
That's only because you're
famous that you get these jobs.

302
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:48,080
I haven't made any unreasonable requests.
You should be thanking me.

303
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:49,700
Excuse me, may I ask?

304
00:24:51,700 --> 00:24:52,940
Didn't you say you were my fan?

305
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:57,760
If you're really a fan, you should
know my personality pretty well, right?

306
00:24:58,500 --> 00:24:59,800
Why do you keep provoking me?

307
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:05,330
What do you mean by that?

308
00:25:05,430 --> 00:25:08,590
When you deal with people, at least
show some consideration for their feelings.

309
00:25:09,900 --> 00:25:11,900
Han Jiwon won't be going back today.

310
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:15,400
I don't need to listen to
your pointless nonsense.

311
00:25:17,500 --> 00:25:18,500
Get lost.

312
00:25:19,700 --> 00:25:21,220
You punk, are you looking for trouble?

313
00:25:24,900 --> 00:25:25,900
Han Jiwon.

314
00:25:26,300 --> 00:25:29,600
Say something, will you? Are you
just going to stand there like a statue?

315
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:34,000
Senior.

316
00:25:39,100 --> 00:25:40,600
Just like Jung-woo said.

317
00:25:42,300 --> 00:25:45,499
I'm not going back today.

318
00:25:45,500 --> 00:25:48,500
So I have no intention of agreeing
to your unreasonable request.

319
00:25:49,100 --> 00:25:50,940
Don't come to me for
help again in the future.

320
00:25:52,900 --> 00:25:56,200
All the times I helped you before,
it was out of my own goodwill.

321
00:25:57,200 --> 00:25:59,076
But that doesn't give you the right
to ask for whatever you want, senior.

322
00:25:59,100 --> 00:26:03,500
Han Jiwon! If you're serving in the military
right now, that could be a huge problem.

323
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:07,680
Because I'm feeling generous
today, I'll let you off the hook.

324
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:13,120
Don't worry, senior.
I don't have to serve in the military.

325
00:26:13,900 --> 00:26:16,620
Because I won the gold medal, I
don't have to serve in the military.

326
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:30,800
Hello?

327
00:26:35,500 --> 00:26:37,220
Am I causing trouble for you by doing this?

328
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:44,000
No, not at all. In fact, I
should be thanking you.

329
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:50,800
That feels amazing.

330
00:26:58,900 --> 00:26:59,900
Han Jiwon.

331
00:27:01,600 --> 00:27:03,100
I was performing normally at first.

332
00:27:06,600 --> 00:27:07,800
Every time I'm in front of you.

333
00:27:10,900 --> 00:27:13,000
I always feel like I'm not myself.

334
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:21,200
Kwon Jungwoo.

335
00:27:22,100 --> 00:27:23,100
What do you mean?

336
00:27:33,300 --> 00:27:34,300
Because...

337
00:27:37,700 --> 00:27:39,500
I think I might be falling for you.

338
00:27:45,300 --> 00:27:46,300
Do you like me?

339
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:04,480
(Next Episode)
Can you leave first?

340
00:28:05,300 --> 00:28:06,400
I can't face you right now.

341
00:28:07,300 --> 00:28:09,030
Did I do something wrong back then?

342
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:11,600
He's really popular, isn't he?

343
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:15,826
Since you're already here, why
not stay the night before you go?

344
00:28:15,851 --> 00:28:17,400
What are you talking about!

345
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:23,070
- So thoughtful.
- I only act this way with you.

346
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:25,676
- If you let your guard down, you could lose.
- Are you talking about me?

347
00:28:25,700 --> 00:28:27,100
Do I just need to win one point?

348
00:28:32,800 --> 00:28:36,800
"Ball Boy Tactics"
